@potus_menu

- @victory
- @defeat_dem
- @defeat_lib
- @house_decides
- @defeat_O

@victory
title: Republicans won the election!
subtitle: Republicans: [+ repEVTotal +] electoral votes
view-if: potus_winner = "rep"
on-arrival: president = Candidate; president_party = "rep";

The Republicans have managed to get a majority of the electors in this election. [? if president == "Wade": The American people have signaled their mandate for Benjamin Wade to serve as President and work with congress. ?][? if president == "Grant": Grant's war career of saving the Union has made an impression on voters. Hopefully he will lead us into a brighter future. ?][? if president == "Chase": Chase is elected president — the Radical Republicans despise him and this could lead to a crisis within the party, but the Moderates and Conservatives are cheering with this return to normalcy in the Executive Mansion. ?]

@defeat_dem
title: The Democrats have won the presidency.
subtitle: Democrats: [+ demEVTotal +] electoral votes
view-if: potus_winner = "dem"
on-arrival: president = "Seymour"; president_party = "dem";

[? if liberal_split = 1 : The Liberal Republican split has handed the election to the Democrats. Horatio Seymour will be the next President of the United States. The damage wrought by the party's division may haunt Reconstruction for years to come. ?][? if liberal_split = 0 : How did you lose this election? It was programmed to be basically impossible to lose! ?]

@defeat_lib
title: The Liberal Republicans have won the presidency!
subtitle: Liberal Republicans: [+ libEVTotal +] electoral votes
view-if: potus_winner = "lib"
on-arrival: president = "Greeley"; president_party = "lib";

In a stunning upset, the Liberal Republican candidate has won a majority of electoral votes. Their platform of reconciliation, civil service reform, and an end to military occupation has resonated with voters weary of Reconstruction's costs and controversies.

@house_decides
title: No majority — the election goes to the House!
subtitle: Rep: [+ repEVTotal +] | Dem: [+ demEVTotal +][? if liberal_split = 1 : | Lib: [+ libEVTotal +] ?]
view-if: potus_winner = "house"
on-arrival: {!
  // House decides — Republican House majority means Republican wins
  if (Q.house_majority >= 2) {
    Q.potus_winner = "rep";
    Q.president = Q.Candidate;
    Q.president_party = "rep";
  } else if (Q.dem_r > Q.rep_r) {
    Q.potus_winner = "dem";
    Q.president = "Seymour";
    Q.president_party = "dem";
  } else {
    Q.potus_winner = "rep";
    Q.president = Q.Candidate;
    Q.president_party = "rep";
  }
!}

No candidate has secured a majority of electoral votes. Under the Constitution, the election is thrown to the House of Representatives, where each state delegation casts a single vote.

[? if house_majority >= 2 : With Republicans controlling a majority of state delegations, the House elects our candidate as President. ?][? if house_majority < 2 : The Democratic-leaning delegations carry the day, and Seymour is elected President by the House. ?]

@defeat_O
title: Something has gone very wrong.
subtitle: Other: [+ otherEVTotal +] votes
view-if: potus_winner = "other"
on-arrival: president = "???"; president_party = "???";

This outcome was not supposed to be possible. Someone has been tampering with the console.

